JUDY WOODRUFF: The tensions
between Saudi
Arabia and Iran continued to
echo throughout

21:59.485 --> 22:05.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Persian Gulf today, as
Kuwait became the
latest Sunni nation to pull its
ambassador

22:05.291 --> 22:09.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from Tehran, though it didn't
fully cut off
diplomatic ties.

22:09.929 --> 22:12.898 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But how is this crisis seen from
Iran?

22:12.932 --> 22:14.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We go to William Brangham for
that.

22:14.767 --> 22:18.170 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
